;line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><strong>2. Show the constraints, not j=
ust the solution</strong></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,5=
5,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Every project has limits. Talking=
 about them makes your work more credible:</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px =
0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">=E2=9C=85 =E2=80=
=9CWe had 3 weeks and a developer handoff deadline, so I prioritized wirefr=
ames and basic interactivity testing over high-fidelity mockups. Given more=
 time, I would have tested more variations.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin:=
 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">This s=
hows you make strategic tradeoffs. That=E2=80=99s a professional skill. Pre=
tending constraints didn=E2=80=99t exist makes you look inexperienced.</p><=
p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-s=
ize: 16px;"><strong>3. Admit what you don=E2=80=99t know or didn=E2=80=99t =
measure</strong></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);lin=
e-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Honesty about gaps is professional:</p><p =
style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-siz=
e: 16px;">=E2=9C=85 =E2=80=9CWe didn=E2=80=99t have analytics instrumentati=
on for this feature, so I can=E2=80=99t provide conversion metrics. What I =
do have is usability test feedback from 5 users and support ticket volume b=
efore and after launch.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: r=
gb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">This shows you understand =
the difference between quantitative and qualitative data. It shows you work=
 with what you have. That=E2=80=99s real-world design.</p><p style=3D"margi=
n: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><str=
ong>4. Talk about what didn=E2=80=99t work</strong></p><p style=3D"margin: =
0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">Failed =
experiments are learning opportunities. Show them:</p><p style=3D"margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">=E2=9C=
=85 =E2=80=9CMy first concept tested poorly. Users found the navigation con=
fusing. I went back, simplified the structure, and the second round of test=
ing showed significant improvement in task completion.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16=
px;">Iteration based on feedback is what design actually is. Showing only s=
uccesses makes you look either inexperienced or dishonest.</p><p style=3D"m=
argin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">=
<strong>5. Be honest about practice projects</strong></p><p style=3D"margin=
: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">If it=
=E2=80=99s a bootcamp project or self-initiated work, just say so. Then mak=
e it rigorous:</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-=
height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">=E2=9C=85 =E2=80=9CThis is a self-initiated =
project. I identified a real problem with my local library=E2=80=99s websit=
e by interviewing 5 regular users. While this didn=E2=80=99t ship, the rese=
arch and design process are real.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px =
0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>Nobody exp=
ects you to only have shipped work if you=E2=80=99re junior. They expect yo=
u to demonstrate thinking. Practice projects are fine if you treat them ser=
iously. </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/a597aeb8-6ad9-422a-=
a016-fd591e618d55?j=3DeyJ1IjoiMWp1ZGpwIn0.5o04gUnkd-Msu0Ib_nbCOLc-sw15-DjXl=
vGx8bWpSeo" rel=3D"" style=3D"color: rgb(54,55,55);text-decoration: underli=
ne;">(Source: Nielsen Norman Group on Portfolios)</a></p><p style=3D"margin=
: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><stro=
ng>6. Use qualitative data when you don=E2=80=99t have quantitative</strong=
></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;=
font-size: 16px;">User quotes, feedback themes, observation notes, support =
ticket reduction, stakeholder reactions. These are all valid forms of impac=
t:</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px=
;font-size: 16px;">=E2=9C=85 =E2=80=9CWhile we didn=E2=80=99t track convers=
ion metrics, we saw support tickets related to checkout drop from ~30/week =
to ~5/week in the month after launch.=E2=80=9D</p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 2=
0px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;">This is real=
 impact, honestly presented.</p><div style=3D"font-size: 16px;line-height: =
26px;"><hr style=3D"margin: 32px 0;padding: 0;height: 1px;background: rgb(0=
