rgin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><=
span>=E2=9C=85 </span><strong>=E2=80=9CI made a mistake in my initial appro=
ach=E2=80=9D</strong><span> This shows self-awareness and learning. Everyon=
e makes mistakes. Acknowledging yours shows maturity.</span></p><p style=3D=
"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;=
"><span>=E2=9C=85 </span><strong>=E2=80=9CI don=E2=80=99t have access to th=
e final metrics=E2=80=9D</strong><span> This is honest about real-world con=
straints. Way better than making numbers up.</span></p><p style=3D"margin: =
0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>=
=E2=9C=85 </span><strong>=E2=80=9CThis was my first time doing [research me=
thod] and here=E2=80=99s what I learned=E2=80=9D</strong><span> Growth mind=
set. Willingness to try new things. Reflective practice. All good signals.<=
/span></p><p style=3D"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: =
26px;font-size: 16px;"><span>=E2=9C=85 </span><strong>=E2=80=9CThe stakehol=
der pushed back on my recommendation and we had to compromise=E2=80=9D</str=
ong><span> This shows you work with real constraints and collaborate with n=
